# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this static HTML portfolio website.

## Changes Made

### 1. Created package.json
- Added `package.json` with `@vercel/analytics` dependency (v1.3.1)
- Configured basic npm scripts for the static site

### 2. Installed Dependencies
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Generated `package-lock.json` for dependency locking

### 3. Configured Analytics in HTML
- Added Vercel Web Analytics script to `index.html` before the closing `</head>` tag
- Used ES module import with CDN-hosted package from jsDelivr
- Implementation uses the official `inject()` function from `@vercel/analytics`

### 4. Created .gitignore
- Added `.gitignore` file to exclude node_modules and other build artifacts

## Technical Details

### Framework Detection
- This is a static HTML portfolio website (vanilla JavaScript)
- No build process or framework like React/Next.js

### Implementation Approach
Following the official Vercel Analytics documentation for static HTML sites:
- Added a `<script type="module">` tag in the HTML head
- Imported `inject` function from CDN: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@vercel/analytics@1/+esm`
- Called `inject()` to initialize analytics tracking

### Code Added to index.html (line 2037-2042):
```html
<!-- Vercel Web Analytics -->
<script type="module">
  import { inject } from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@vercel/analytics@1/+esm';
  inject();
</script>
```

## Next Steps for Deployment

1. **Enable Analytics in Vercel Dashboard**
   - Navigate to your project in the Vercel dashboard
   - Go to the Analytics section
   - Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics

2. **Deploy to Vercel**
   - Push these changes to your repository
   - Vercel will automatically deploy
   - Analytics will start tracking page views once deployed

3. **Verification**
   - After deployment, visit your site
   - Open browser DevTools > Network tab
   - Look for requests to Vercel analytics endpoints
   - View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

## Files Modified
- `index.html` - Added analytics script in head section

## Files Created
- `package.json` - Project configuration with analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Dependency lock file
- `.gitignore` - Git ignore rules for node_modules and build artifacts
- `.vade-report` - This implementation report

## Testing
- Build script executed successfully (static site, no build required)
- HTML syntax verified - analytics script properly inserted before closing head tag
- No linting errors introduced

## Notes
- The analytics script uses a CDN approach, which is perfect for static sites
- The `inject()` function will automatically track page views
- Analytics only tracks in production (not in development/localhost)
- The package is installed locally for potential future use of custom events
